<br>
I believe in a higher power that resides within every living thing.  A step above the concept of the Transcendental Oversoul.  I strongly believe in reincarnation and the idea that souls live on.  I know they do, because I knew the exact second when my Grandma died, even though I wasn't there. I know when she visited me, and I knew when she decided to move on to the next life.  I'm just glad she stuck around for my wedding reception. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I also believe in the concept of a messianic age, and that it is our responsibility to make the world the best that we possibly can in our lifetimes until it is such a pure place that the messiah can come.  The whole reincarnation thing is to return to do as much good as possible until we can rest. Of course, once the world IS that pure, we wouldn't need a savior because we would have saved ourselves, and honestly, I think that IS the whole point.  I believe that God - the messiah - the creator - the spirit that twists our fates resides inside of each of us, whether or not we choose to recognize it.  It's our creativity, our inspiration, the bit of good that fundamentally overrides the crap that each of us could become.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, I do not believe that all wars occur in the name of God, but rather in the name of money.  Even in Christianity, when it became bastardized into Catholicism and all of the old ways that used to be a part of it became heresy it was all about having all the money go to the same place.  It was all about power, and it still is.<br>
<br>
I think that outright denial of a higher power is both arrogant and ignorant.  Things came together - the universe in all of its spledor and mystery - in ways we don't understand, and that we certainly did not create.  I do believe in science.  I do believe there are explanations.  But I also believe that in curiousity there is imagination, in imagination, hope, and in hope, both excitement and love, and for me, that's what the little part of God in me exists for.<br>
<br>
If you question, by all means do so. I was agnostic for *years* but never ultimately an athiest.  There are too many wonderful things that we have nothing to do with in this world to believe that we are the most powerful beings in existance. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dashofmooo>Dash Of Mooo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/Strobe.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/thumbs/leann2b.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Moooo!!<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-vip.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 10/14/02 2:20:32 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: -</span><hr size=1> Beautifull!<br>
